title: WEEK 7: Region title, playoff races take shape after big night
text:
+1 By AccessWDUN Staff 
The state playoff and region title picture began to take a little better shape after some key matchups Friday night. 
In Region 8- , Lanier held off a late Gainesville rally for a 16-8 win to grab sole possession of first place in the region. Also in 8- , Flowery Branch traveled to Clarke Central and notched a 28-21 victory. 
Meanwhile, Dawson County grabbed sole possession of first in Region 7-AAA, winning a 54-40 shootout over Franklin County. Elsewhere in 7-AAA, East Hall beat West Hall 24-7 and Fannin County held off Lumpkin County 41-35 as both teams stayed in contention. 
In Region 8-AA Union County and Rabun County both took big wins to set up a showdown for first place next week in Tiger. 
In Region 8-AAAA, Buford rolled over North Hall while Stephens County nipped White County 21-20 to remain unbeaten -- the Wolves and Indians are the only teams left undefeated in 8-AAAA play. 
Jefferson maintained full control of Region 8-AAA, shutting down Morgan County 17-0, while Elbert County fended off Jackson County's strong effort, 20-14. 
Be sure to check out our Friday Game Night page for detailed game stories from around northeast Georgia, as well as video highlights from a night of gridiron action.
